          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 7320,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "When publishing a commercial communication, social media influencer shall ensure that its commercial intent is clearly and prominently disclosed to the public. The disclosure must: 1) use clear, universally understood terminology; 2) visible at the beginning of the content, before the core promotional message is conveyed, and must remain visible throughout the entirety of the content's display; 3) The disclosure must identify the trader (the company paying for the promotion) on whose behalf the commercial communication is being made.",
